### ============================================
### API Key Authentication
### ============================================
# AdminApi uses API key authentication via:
# 1. Authorization header (preferred): Authorization: Bearer <api-key>
# 2. Query parameter (fallback): ?apikey=<api-key>
#
# The API key must belong to a user with SysAdmin role.
# Tenant ID can be provided via:
# - Query parameter: ?tenantId=<tenant-id>
# - Route parameter: /tenants/{tenantId}/...
# - X-Tenant-Id header: X-Tenant-Id: <tenant-id>

### ============================================
### Agent Management (X-Tenant-Id required)
### ============================================

### List Agent Instances
# Get all agents deployed in a tenant with optional pagination
# Tenant ID can be provided via route parameter (in URL) or X-Tenant-Id header
# Optional query parameters: page, pageSize
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}/agents?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Agent Instance
# Get details of a specific agent by MongoDB ObjectId
# Tenant ID can be provided via route parameter (in URL) or X-Tenant-Id header
# Note: Uses MongoDB ObjectId (not agent name) - get from list agents response
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}/agents/{{agentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Update Agent Instance
# Update agent instance (name, description, onboardingJson)
# Tenant ID can be provided via route parameter (in URL) or X-Tenant-Id header
# Note: Uses MongoDB ObjectId (not agent name) - get from list agents response
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}/agents/{{agentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "description": "Updated agent description",
  "onboardingJson": "{\"description\":\"Updated agent description\"}"
}

###

### Delete Agent Instance
# Delete an agent instance by MongoDB ObjectId
# Tenant ID can be provided via route parameter (in URL) or X-Tenant-Id header
# Note: Uses MongoDB ObjectId (not agent name) - get from list agents response
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}/agents/{{agentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}
Accept: application/json

